			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">An interesting and useful tactic for mage pets is to use them as "blockers".
<br />

<br />
When you have adds inc, they will often run for healers/debuffers/mezzers. These people need protected.
<br />

<br />
Today it's much easier to selectively block these with the pet, here is how:
<br />

<br />
When INC is announced, and you use /assist, you will see what mob the main tank is going for. The leadership AA which gives a target ring to the Main Assist's target really helps here. Now, your task is to stop any OTHER mob.
<br />
Your pet can stop and gain aggro long enough for debuffers/CC/Mezzers to work. And here is the beauty of pets: <span style="font-weight: bold"> when mezz lands, the pet won't break it!</span>
<br />

<br />
To aid in this, you want a pet that is tough and can aggro, epic and air pets are usually the best, though you may use earth. Adding things like gnoll hide lariats to pets also improves this (stun and aggro). If you can, get your pet Virtued, Focus, Temperance or the like to increase hps, plus summoned items with +hps.
<br />

<br />
How I work this system is:
<br />
Mobs are inc, check MA target, then I order pet to intercept and hit mobs he's not on, EACH ONE if possible, maybe using "back off" and "attack" in sequence. I do this using the pet window command, because my hot key for pet attack is:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">/pet back off   /pet kill    /pet kill</span>
<br />
So I have the additional mobs on pet's hate list. So it should buy time, if I hit my hot key the pet WILL switch targets, so I can get it back onto the MA's target, or one not successfully mezzed and about to kill the enchanter.
<br />
Having Calliav's on the pet helps especially against hard hitters.
<br />
 
<br />
