				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use this alot.
<br />

<br />
I like to stand slightly behind and to the side of the mezzers/healers.  I then turn slightly so the MA and his normal fighting position is not in my view but I can see the area the mobs have to cross to get to the mezzer/healers.  I can still assist the MA to target the mob and nuke it.  However, if any mob comes into my view, I can use the "Target nearest NPC key" {I have remapped it to my H key, don't remember what it is normally" and then hit my pet attack macro.  This way I can switch my pet my using two keystrokes.  It is much faster than trying to target them with a mouse.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
