			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use this method a bit myself, always sending pets in adds so mezzers / CC can work their magic.
<br />

<br />
However I always  had a problem  tageting the right mob, considering when the puller gets adds they usually come in droves right on top of each other. 
<br />

<br />
I have since found out how to use a cycle target 'key'. This allows me to /assist MA when i see he has adds, hit my cycle target key (my target moves to the NEXT available mob) and then i send in pet. 
<br />

<br />
This also works wonders in Nro LDONs where I AM the Crowd Control. If theres more then 1 add, hitting the 'Cycle target' key after mezzing the first add will target the SECOND ADD  and NOT the one the MA is attacking (assumming you /assited then cycled).
<br />

<br />
For me the cycle target key wasnt mapped, but I had been playing my mage before this feature was implemented a few months back ... Im not sure if there is a default mapping.  But regardless it can be changed under OPTIONS, KEYBORD and then TARGET (I think that how it goes, Im at work so i can verify)
<br />

<br />
FYI ... my cycle target key is <span style="font-weight: bold">|</span>  <span style="font-style: italic">(pipe)</span>
<br />

<br />
Eanelder</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
