				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yeah, it's fun when pet does what I think it should do everytime - zoom in and land a couple hits, a bash, and a stun proc in short order.  If things go well, its shield (I use MS4) will eat the intial hit and its buffs (around 8k raid buffed) will allow it to absorb a couple rounds.  This should be enough time for chanters or off-tanks to respond.  Some prefer using earth pet, but that is unreliable in its timing...pet may end up rooting next to healers who may be unable to move out of the way due to heal rotation.  That's why I prefer to rely on stuns and bashes.<br />_________________<br />TJRii
